misconceptions.inferred_category_name: No bug / correct array-shift mental model
misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that to right-shift an array by one with wrap-around, you must (1) save the last element, (2) move elements from right to left to avoid overwriting values, and (3) place the saved last element into index 0.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No conceptual gap detected. This matches Java’s actual execution model: assignments overwrite array cells, so iterating from N-1 down to 1 preserves needed values; storing the last element prevents it from being lost.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: None; produces correct output for all valid inputs, including N=0 or N=1 (the N>0 guard prevents out-of-bounds).
